name: Doudna Fine Arts Center
directions: Second floor by the music wing elevator. Near the piano faculty offices.
comment: There are two. They used to be gendered so only one had a period pad box, and only one has a urinal. They are both marked gender neutral though.

name: Starbucks
directions: Two gender neutral restrooms available to the left of the front counter

name: redmill burgers
comment: great burgers and milkshakes and 2 single stall gender neutral restrooms

name: 2nd St. Gallery
directions: In the back room (connected to the front, just an open space) there is an unmarked door that is typically opened. Go in and there will be a sign leading to it with the unisex bathroom symbol, but if you don't see it, it will be to the right at the end of the hall.
comment: The staff are quite nice. If the door in the back room is open you can go right in (and can do so regardless), but if you're nervous you can ask and they will very likely show you to it.

name: Starbucks
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Tavares Public Library
directions: All the bathrooms on premises are gender neutral.

name: Play N Learn
directions: On the right hand wall as you enter

name: L'Experience
directions: In the back, with clear sign pointing to restroom.

name: Harvest Foods
directions: Back of the store, through the produce or paper product section

name: Safeway
directions: Left-front corner of the store

name: Jo-Ann Fabrics
directions: Straight from the front doors to the back of the store, just on the right-hand side
comment: Just act like you're browsing for a bit

name: Walla Walla Clinic: General Surgery, Podiatry & Urology
directions: Just across the hall from the nurse's station, which is behind a door from the waiting room.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic: Laboratory
directions: Across from an exam room
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic: Orthopedics & Radiology
directions: Down the left-hand hall, first door on the right, just behind the reception area
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic: Allergy & Endocrinology
directions: Near the nurse's station
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic: Internal Medicine & Gastroenterology
directions: Just outside the waiting room, across from the elevator
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic: Walk-In Clinic
directions: Around the corner from the waiting room, near the elevator. Next to it, there is a 2nd gender-neutral restroom that is not accessible and does not have a changing table.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic: Pediatrics
directions: In the back left corner of the waiting room
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Total Wine & More Bloomington
directions: in the back
comment: Their 2 single-user restrooms have been relabelled as gender neutral as of January 2020

name: Lonesome Rose
directions: There are two single unisex bathrooms between the restaurant seating and the bar area. You can enter and exit the building from the bar side or the restaurant side.

name: Harmony’s Brewing Company
directions: Past the entrance, you’ll go slightly to the right as you get further into the restaurant. To your right will be stairs, to the left are two single stall gender neutral bathrooms.
comment: You’ll probably have to be a customer. Restroom is clean and spacious.

name: Setauket Presbyterian Church
directions: The restroom opposite the church office.

name: EQuality center
directions: The entire building
comment: Safe space

name: burger king
directions: all the way in the back of the restaurant by the back of the kitchen
comment: door is usually unlocked if not you can ask they’re usually friendly

name: Starbucks
comment: Probably for customers only

name: Filmstreams Dundee Theater/Lola’s Café
directions: Enter through the back parking lot and then walk straight ahead, take a right at the Lola’a Café side. Single stall/all gender bathroom is located in the back corridor next to the Linder Microcinema.
comment: Anyone can use this restroom, no questions asked. Menstrual products are located under the sink in every restroom, as well!

name: Filmstreams Dundee Theater/Lola’s Café
directions: Enter through the back parking lot, walk straight ahead, and take a right. Single stall restroom is located on the back corridor by the Linder Microcinema on the Lola’s Café side!
comment: No questions asked, anyone can use this restroom. Menstrual products are stocked under the sink in every bathroom as well!

name: Vika Kino
directions: First floor, across from "Sal 1" - at the back.

name: Vega Scene
directions: Third floor, by the stairs. There is an elevator.
comment: Vega Scene is both host to a movie theatre/stage and a café, so it is fairly easy to go there regardless of whether you're a patron.

name: Priesterweg
comment: Costa 0,50€

name: Chipotle
directions: Off of the dining area by the drinks, utensil area

name: Fork and Gavel
directions: In the back, past the drink coolers.
comment: Counter service restaurant. If not hungry, buy a pastry or non-alcoholic drink. Has gender neural signage on their single use bathrooms.

name: Village Restaurant
directions: There are 2 tiny single use bathrooms in this diner.
comment: Diner, need to be a paying customer. But people go in there to get a pastry to go, so get one and while they wrap it up, use the bathroom. Waitresses there are nice despite being flat out busy most of the time.

name: Flock
directions: At the back of the cafe on the right.
comment: Queer friendly business

name: La Avellaneda
directions: Único baño unisex

name: The Happy Hawaiian Lashes
directions: 2nd floor

name: Poppins
directions: Right at the back
comment: Single occupancy, gendered stalls

name: Costa Coffee
directions: At the back, on the right

name: Waitrose
directions: Past the checkouts

name: Bookshop Alehouse
directions: On the right, just past the bar

name: Casa
directions: To the right of the entrance
comment: Ask front desk for permission first

name: The grand taproom
directions: In the basement in the taproom

name: Red Door Grill - Brookside
directions: To the right, and all the way to the back, past the stairs.
comment: Gendered restrooms, but you walk into the area, and there are two shared sinks. On the right are two doors for "womens" and on the left are two doors for "mens". Each is a fully enclosed room with a toilet. The door is frosted, but I could not see shapes through it, only light while inside (from the outside, I couldn't see anything, as the lights in the room are before the toilet). The locks say occupied on the outside when locked.

name: Sacramento County Administraton Building
directions: 2 Single person gender neutral bathrooms on ground floor across from elevators. There may be more on additional levels but I haven't been up on those floors to see.
comment: Public building.  Open during normal business hours

name: Exploratory Hall
directions: On the lower level by the vending machines southeast side of the building

name: Harper College Building M
directions: Just past front desk to the left by the vending machines
comment: You need to have a gym membership or be present with a member

name: Grover Cleveland Service Area
directions: In between men and women’s
comment: Family bathroom

name: Tim Hortons (Bury)
directions: Upstairs at the back

name: Community Co-op
directions: Go to the back of the store, in front of the coolers, and go left. It should be next to a ramp, but not up the ramp.
comment: The store is mostly accessable. There are ramps going into the store. The doors are not automatic and can be tricky if you have a wheelchair or stroller.

name: Swan and Talbot
directions: To the left as you come through the back door.
comment: Staff are all trans friendly :)

name: Public rest rooms
directions: Public restrooms including one family restroom
comment: As of this writing the view of the family restroom is obscured from outside, but you can see it once you enter.

name: Argyros Forum
directions: First floor. Find the area by the elevators, and with the male/female bathrooms on your right and Amazonocker on your left, head down the hall and turn right. The bathroom will be to your left just before exiting the back doors.

name: Wingstop
comment: A key is usually required from the front.

name: 99 Cents Only
directions: In the back, to the right

name: Walmart
directions: In the back, towards the middle of the store. Near the electronics department.

name: Dunkin Donuts
directions: In the back to the right

name: CVS
directions: In the back to the left

name: Henson Science Hall, Salisbury University
directions: Middle section of the building, both 2nd and 3rd floors

name: The Centre At Salisbury
directions: Middle of the mall near Verizon. Walk all the way down the hallway till you see a gender neutral family restroom.

name: Chocolateria
directions: Walk all the way to the back wall when you enter, take a left, and it’s to your left!

name: Dish
directions: By the bar in the back
comment: In a restaurant

name: Dunkin' Donuts
directions: Straight in the back

name: Becker College Borger Academic Center
directions: First floor by seating area with tables and plastic chairs. 2 bathrooms on opposite sides. If entering from parking lot, one is right there facing you and the other you have to walk around the tables to get to.
comment: The bathroom closest to the parking lot entrance has a toilet while the one opposite it has a urinal as well.

name: Becker College Fuller Campus Center
directions: Walk all the way through the lobby to the hallway, there are 2 gender neutral bathrooms on the left.

name: Erik's
directions: When you walk in front doors on the right, they are to the right
comment: Coverted single stall gendered restrooms into gender neutral restrooms

name: Marshall Rec Center
directions: Gender neutral/Family bathroom in between stairs and elevator
comment: Marshall Student or have a gym membership there

name: Taco Bell
directions: Enter through the doors on the parking lot side of the restaurant. Restrooms are in a hallway to the right.
comment: Not sure if they want you to be a customer, but entering through those side doors allows you to bypass the counter. No one should notice you if you slip in to use the restroom.

name: Evolution Games
directions: As soon as you walk in, go straight down the hall in front of you. The male and female restrooms are along the hall to the left, as well as a gender neutral restroom right after that.
comment: Theyre fairly friendly here and dont mind if youre not a paying customer, are just here to hang out, or are just here to use the restrooms! Also allow ftm and mtf trans in the correct bathrooms corresponding to their gender along with a gender neutral option. Feel free to stay for a round of Dungeons and Dragons or Magic the Gathering though! :)

name: Highlander Union Building
directions: Second floor, to the right of the elevators from the east side there are double doors that open to a hallway. first door on the left is a bathroom.

name: SLC Tim hortons
directions: Turn left as soon as you're in the timmies and there are 2 options for bathrooms!

name: Canyon Creek North
directions: In the lobby, go up to the elevators, turn to your right and it should be right in front of you. (it's a bit hidden behind the front desk.)
comment: Open to all. Building my be locked after hours or during school breaks.

name: Student Union
directions: Hallway near the pub, across from the gaming room.
comment: Open to all. Knock first.

name: Walmart Supercenter
directions: Go to the back of the store behind the shoe section. On the left you will see a desk for layaway. On the right will be normal public restrooms. There is a gray door marked Family Restroom straight ahead
comment: Although the front of the store has restrooms too, the back is the only place there's a gender neutral one

name: Pasta Factory
directions: There are two single person restrooms inside the Banquet Room, which is a separated from the main building. There is a sign on the door indicating it is part of the same restaurant. There are another two at the bottom of the staircase that separates Pasta and Pizza. These ones have a single door you have to enter first and then you will see the two for the actual restrooms
comment: You may use the Banquet restrooms even if you are not part of a buffet group. The one on the right seems to be a little dirtier than the other

name: Community Co-op
directions: Go to the back of the store where the coolers are and take a left. It should be next to a ramp, but not up a ramp.
comment: It is mostly accessable. There are ramps leading into the building. The doors are not automatic and can be difficult to navigate with strollers or wheelchairs, but staff will help with the doors.

name: Lyft Driver Center
directions: In the back of the building
comment: Mixed gender bathroom with 4 regular stalls and 1 ADA stall. May only be available for Lyft riders and drivers

name: Buchanan-Haralson Public Library
directions: In the back of the library by the staircase. Ask the librarian for help if needed!

name: IVC B-200 Building
directions: Use directory to find B200 building. Two all-gender, accessible bathrooms are located at the bottom of the stairwell, directly across the hall from two gendered restrooms.
comment: Park in the church parking lot to avoid paying to park.

name: IVC B-200 Building
directions: Use a directory to find the B200 building (you'll know when you've found it, all the buildings have obvious sinage). There are two accessible, all-gender bathrooms at the bottom of the stairwell on the first floor.
comment: Parking in the church parking lot to the left of Lot 1 will bring you close, and you won't have to worry about paying for parking.

name: Bean and Barley
directions: Straight back and to the left

name: The Good Earth
directions: In the back near the kitchen/desk.
comment: No need to buy anything.
